2024/// Support for the ObjFW runtime.
2025class CGObjCObjFW: public CGObjCGNU {
2026protected:
2027 /// The GCC ABI message lookup function. Returns an IMP pointing to the
2028 /// method implementation for this message.
2029 LazyRuntimeFunction MsgLookupFn;
2030 /// stret lookup function. While this does not seem to make sense at the
2031 /// first look, this is required to call the correct forwarding function.
2032 LazyRuntimeFunction MsgLookupFnSRet;
2033 /// The GCC ABI superclass message lookup function. Takes a pointer to a
2034 /// structure describing the receiver and the class, and a selector as
2035 /// arguments. Returns the IMP for the corresponding method.
2036 LazyRuntimeFunction MsgLookupSuperFn, MsgLookupSuperFnSRet;
2037
2038 llvm::Value *LookupIMP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *&Receiver,
2039 llvm::Value *cmd, llvm::MDNode *node,
2040 MessageSendInfo &MSI) override {
2041 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2042 llvm::Value *args[] = {
2043 EnforceType(Builder, Receiver, IdTy),
2044 EnforceType(Builder, cmd, SelectorTy) };
2045
2046 llvm::CallBase *imp;
2047 if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesSRet(MSI.CallInfo))
2048 imp = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(MsgLookupFnSRet, args);
2049 else
2050 imp = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(MsgLookupFn, args);
2051
2052 imp->setMetadata(msgSendMDKind, node);
2053 return imp;
2054 }
2055
2056 llvm::Value *LookupIMPSuper(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address ObjCSuper,
2057 llvm::Value *cmd, MessageSendInfo &MSI) override {
2058 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2059 llvm::Value *lookupArgs[] = {
2060 EnforceType(Builder, ObjCSuper.getPointer(), PtrToObjCSuperTy), cmd,
2061 };
2062
2063 if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesSRet(MSI.CallInfo))
2064 return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(MsgLookupSuperFnSRet, lookupArgs);
2065 else
2066 return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(MsgLookupSuperFn, lookupArgs);
2067 }
2068
2069 llvm::Value *GetClassNamed(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const std::string &Name,
2070 bool isWeak) override {
2071 if (isWeak)
2072 return CGObjCGNU::GetClassNamed(CGF, Name, isWeak);
2073
2074 EmitClassRef(Name);
2075 std::string SymbolName = "_OBJC_CLASS_" + Name;
2076 llvm::GlobalVariable *ClassSymbol = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(SymbolName);
2077 if (!ClassSymbol)
2078 ClassSymbol = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, LongTy, false,
2079 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
2080 nullptr, SymbolName);
2081 return ClassSymbol;
2082 }
2083
2084public:
2085 CGObjCObjFW(CodeGenModule &Mod): CGObjCGNU(Mod, 9, 3) {
2086 // IMP objc_msg_lookup(id, SEL);
2087 MsgLookupFn.init(&CGM, "objc_msg_lookup", IMPTy, IdTy, SelectorTy);
2088 MsgLookupFnSRet.init(&CGM, "objc_msg_lookup_stret", IMPTy, IdTy,
2089 SelectorTy);
2090 // IMP objc_msg_lookup_super(struct objc_super*, SEL);
2091 MsgLookupSuperFn.init(&CGM, "objc_msg_lookup_super", IMPTy,
2092 PtrToObjCSuperTy, SelectorTy);
2093 MsgLookupSuperFnSRet.init(&CGM, "objc_msg_lookup_super_stret", IMPTy,
2094 PtrToObjCSuperTy, SelectorTy);
2095 }
2096};
2097} // end anonymous namespace

2099/// Emits a reference to a dummy variable which is emitted with each class.
2100/// This ensures that a linker error will be generated when trying to link
2101/// together modules where a referenced class is not defined.
2102void CGObjCGNU::EmitClassRef(const std::string &className) {
2103 std::string symbolRef = "__objc_class_ref_" + className;
2104 // Don't emit two copies of the same symbol
2105 if (TheModule.getGlobalVariable(symbolRef))
2106 return;
2107 std::string symbolName = "__objc_class_name_" + className;
2108 llvm::GlobalVariable *ClassSymbol = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(symbolName);
2109 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2110 if (!ClassSymbol) {
2111 ClassSymbol = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, LongTy, false,
2112 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
2113 nullptr, symbolName, nullptr,
2114 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
2115 AS);
2116 }
2117 new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, ClassSymbol->getType(), true,
2118 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, ClassSymbol, symbolRef, nullptr,
2119 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
2120}

2274 WeakReadFn.init(&CGM, "objc_read_weak", IdTy, PtrToIdTy);
2275 // void *objc_memmove_collectable(void*, void *, size_t);
2276 MemMoveFn.init(&CGM, "objc_memmove_collectable", PtrTy, PtrTy, PtrTy,
2277 SizeTy);
2278 }
2279}
2280
2281llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GetClassNamed(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2282 const std::string &Name, bool isWeak) {
2283 llvm::Constant *ClassName = MakeConstantString(Name);
2284 // With the incompatible ABI, this will need to be replaced with a direct
2285 // reference to the class symbol. For the compatible nonfragile ABI we are
2286 // still performing this lookup at run time but emitting the symbol for the
2287 // class externally so that we can make the switch later.
2288 //
2289 // Libobjc2 contains an LLVM pass that replaces calls to objc_lookup_class
2290 // with memoized versions or with static references if it's safe to do so.
2291 if (!isWeak)
2292 EmitClassRef(Name);
2293
2294 llvm::FunctionCallee ClassLookupFn = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
2295 llvm::FunctionType::get(IdTy, PtrToInt8Ty, true), "objc_lookup_class");
2296 return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ClassLookupFn, ClassName);
2297}
2298
2299// This has to perform the lookup every time, since posing and related
2300// techniques can modify the name -> class mapping.
2301llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GetClass(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2302 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID) {
2303 auto *Value =
2304 GetClassNamed(CGF, OID->getNameAsString(), OID->isWeakImported());
2305 if (auto *ClassSymbol = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Value))
2306 CGM.setGVProperties(ClassSymbol, OID);
2307 return Value;
2308}
2309
2310llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::EmitNSAutoreleasePoolClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
2311 auto *Value = GetClassNamed(CGF, "NSAutoreleasePool", false);
2312 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
2313 if (auto *ClassSymbol = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Value)) {
2314 IdentifierInfo &II = CGF.CGM.getContext().Idents.get("NSAutoreleasePool");
2315 TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
2316 DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
2317
2318 const VarDecl *VD = nullptr;
2319 for (const auto &Result : DC->lookup(&II))
2320 if ((VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
2321 break;
2322
2323 CGM.setGVProperties(ClassSymbol, VD);
2324 }
2325 }
2326 return Value;
2327}
2328
2329llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GetTypedSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Selector Sel,
2330 const std::string &TypeEncoding) {
2331 SmallVectorImpl<TypedSelector> &Types = SelectorTable[Sel];
2332 llvm::GlobalAlias *SelValue = nullptr;
2333
2334 for (SmallVectorImpl<TypedSelector>::iterator i = Types.begin(),
2335 e = Types.end() ; i!=e ; i++) {
2336 if (i->first == TypeEncoding) {
2337 SelValue = i->second;
2338 break;
2339 }
2340 }
2341 if (!SelValue) {
2342 SelValue = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(
2343 SelectorTy->getElementType(), CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS(),
2344 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, ".objc_selector_" +
2345 Sel.getAsString(), &TheModule);
2346 Types.emplace_back(TypeEncoding, SelValue);
2347 }
2348
2349 return SelValue;
2350}
2351
2352Address CGObjCGNU::GetAddrOfSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Selector Sel) {
2353 llvm::Value *SelValue = GetSelector(CGF, Sel);
2354
2355 // Store it to a temporary. Does this satisfy the semantics of
2356 // GetAddrOfSelector? Hopefully.
2357 Address tmp = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(SelValue->getType(),
2358 CGF.getPointerAlign());
2359 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(SelValue, tmp);
2360 return tmp;
2361}
2362
2363llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GetSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Selector Sel) {
2364 return GetTypedSelector(CGF, Sel, std::string());
2365}
2366
2367llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GetSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2368 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
2369 std::string SelTypes = CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(Method);
2370 return GetTypedSelector(CGF, Method->getSelector(), SelTypes);
2371}
2372
2373llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::GetEHType(QualType T) {
2374 if (T->isObjCIdType() || T->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
2375 // With the old ABI, there was only one kind of catchall, which broke
2376 // foreign exceptions. With the new ABI, we use __objc_id_typeinfo as
2377 // a pointer indicating object catchalls, and NULL to indicate real
2378 // catchalls
2379 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
2380 return MakeConstantString("@id");
2381 } else {
2382 return nullptr;
2383 }
2384 }
2385
2386 // All other types should be Objective-C interface pointer types.
2387 const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT = T->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
2388 assert(OPT && "Invalid @catch type.");
2389 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *IDecl = OPT->getObjectType()->getInterface();
2390 assert(IDecl && "Invalid @catch type.");
2391 return MakeConstantString(IDecl->getIdentifier()->getName());
2392}
2393
2394llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNUstep::GetEHType(QualType T) {
2395 if (usesSEHExceptions)
2396 return CGM.getCXXABI().getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(T);
2397
2398 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2399 return CGObjCGNU::GetEHType(T);
2400
2401 // For Objective-C++, we want to provide the ability to catch both C++ and
2402 // Objective-C objects in the same function.
2403
2404 // There's a particular fixed type info for 'id'.
2405 if (T->isObjCIdType() ||
2406 T->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
2407 llvm::Constant *IDEHType =
2408 CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable("__objc_id_type_info");
2409 if (!IDEHType)
2410 IDEHType =
2411 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), PtrToInt8Ty,
2412 false,
2413 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
2414 nullptr, "__objc_id_type_info");
2415 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(IDEHType, PtrToInt8Ty);
2416 }
2417
2418 const ObjCObjectPointerType *PT =
2419 T->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
2420 assert(PT && "Invalid @catch type.");
2421 const ObjCInterfaceType *IT = PT->getInterfaceType();
2422 assert(IT && "Invalid @catch type.");
2423 std::string className = IT->getDecl()->getIdentifier()->getName();
2424
2425 std::string typeinfoName = "__objc_eh_typeinfo_" + className;
2426
2427 // Return the existing typeinfo if it exists
2428 llvm::Constant *typeinfo = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(typeinfoName);
2429 if (typeinfo)
2430 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(typeinfo, PtrToInt8Ty);
2431
2432 // Otherwise create it.
2433
2434 // vtable for gnustep::libobjc::__objc_class_type_info
2435 // It's quite ugly hard-coding this. Ideally we'd generate it using the host
2436 // platform's name mangling.
2437 const char *vtableName = "_ZTVN7gnustep7libobjc22__objc_class_type_infoE";
2438 auto *Vtable = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(vtableName);
2439 if (!Vtable) {
2440 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2441 Vtable = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, PtrToInt8Ty, true,
2442 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
2443 nullptr, vtableName, nullptr,
2444 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
2445 AS);
2446 }
2447 llvm::Constant *Two = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 2);
2448 auto *BVtable = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
2449 llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Vtable->getValueType(), Vtable, Two),
2450 PtrToInt8Ty);
2451
2452 llvm::Constant *typeName =
2453 ExportUniqueString(className, "__objc_eh_typename_");
2454
2455 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
2456 auto fields = builder.beginStruct();
2457 fields.add(BVtable);
2458 fields.add(typeName);
2459 llvm::Constant *TI =
2460 fields.finishAndCreateGlobal("__objc_eh_typeinfo_" + className,
2461 CGM.getPointerAlign(),
2462 /*constant*/ false,
2463 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
2464 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(TI, PtrToInt8Ty);
2465}
2466
2467/// Generate an NSConstantString object.
2468ConstantAddress CGObjCGNU::GenerateConstantString(const StringLiteral *SL) {
2469
2470 std::string Str = SL->getString().str();
2471 CharUnits Align = CGM.getPointerAlign();
2472
2473 // Look for an existing one
2474 llvm::StringMap<llvm::Constant*>::iterator old = ObjCStrings.find(Str);
2475 if (old != ObjCStrings.end())
2476 return ConstantAddress(old->getValue(), Align);
2477
2478 StringRef StringClass = CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCConstantStringClass;
2479
2480 if (StringClass.empty()) StringClass = "NSConstantString";
2481
2482 std::string Sym = "_OBJC_CLASS_";
2483 Sym += StringClass;
2484
2485 llvm::Constant *isa = TheModule.getNamedGlobal(Sym);
2486
2487 if (!isa) {
2488 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2489 isa = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, IdTy, /* isConstant */false,
2490 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage, nullptr, Sym, nullptr,
2491 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
2492 } else if (isa->getType() != PtrToIdTy)
2493 isa = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(isa, PtrToIdTy);
2494
2495 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
2496 auto Fields = Builder.beginStruct();
2497 Fields.add(isa);
2498 Fields.add(MakeConstantString(Str));
2499 Fields.addInt(IntTy, Str.size());
2500 llvm::Constant *ObjCStr =
2501 Fields.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_str", Align);
2502 ObjCStr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(ObjCStr, PtrToInt8Ty);
2503 ObjCStrings[Str] = ObjCStr;
2504 ConstantStrings.push_back(ObjCStr);
2505 return ConstantAddress(ObjCStr, Align);
2506}
2507
2508///Generates a message send where the super is the receiver. This is a message
2509///send to self with special delivery semantics indicating which class's method
2510///should be called.
2511RValue
2512CGObjCGNU::GenerateMessageSendSuper(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2513 ReturnValueSlot Return,
2514 QualType ResultType,
2515 Selector Sel,
2516 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
2517 bool isCategoryImpl,
2518 llvm::Value *Receiver,
2519 bool IsClassMessage,
2520 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
2521 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
2522 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2523 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::GCOnly) {
2524 if (Sel == RetainSel || Sel == AutoreleaseSel) {
2525 return RValue::get(EnforceType(Builder, Receiver,
2526 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(ResultType)));
2527 }
2528 if (Sel == ReleaseSel) {
2529 return RValue::get(nullptr);
2530 }
2531 }
2532
2533 llvm::Value *cmd = GetSelector(CGF, Sel);
2534 CallArgList ActualArgs;
2535
2536 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(EnforceType(Builder, Receiver, IdTy)), ASTIdTy);
2537 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(cmd), CGF.getContext().getObjCSelType());
2538 ActualArgs.addFrom(CallArgs);
2539
2540 MessageSendInfo MSI = getMessageSendInfo(Method, ResultType, ActualArgs);
2541 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2542
2543 llvm::Value *ReceiverClass = nullptr;
2544 bool isV2ABI = isRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GNUstep, 2);
2545 if (isV2ABI) {
2546 ReceiverClass = GetClassNamed(CGF,
2547 Class->getSuperClass()->getNameAsString(), /*isWeak*/false);
2548 if (IsClassMessage) {
2549 // Load the isa pointer of the superclass is this is a class method.
2550 ReceiverClass = Builder.CreateBitCast(
2551 ReceiverClass, CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(IdTy));
2552 ReceiverClass =
2553 Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ReceiverClass, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2554 }
2555 ReceiverClass = EnforceType(Builder, ReceiverClass, IdTy);
2556 } else {
2557 if (isCategoryImpl) {
2558 llvm::FunctionCallee classLookupFunction = nullptr;
2559 if (IsClassMessage) {
2560 classLookupFunction = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(
2561 IdTy, PtrTy, true), "objc_get_meta_class");
2562 } else {
2563 classLookupFunction = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(
2564 IdTy, PtrTy, true), "objc_get_class");
2565 }
2566 ReceiverClass = Builder.CreateCall(classLookupFunction,
2567 MakeConstantString(Class->getNameAsString()));
2568 } else {
2569 // Set up global aliases for the metaclass or class pointer if they do not
2570 // already exist. These will are forward-references which will be set to
2571 // pointers to the class and metaclass structure created for the runtime
2572 // load function. To send a message to super, we look up the value of the
2573 // super_class pointer from either the class or metaclass structure.
2574 if (IsClassMessage) {
2575 if (!MetaClassPtrAlias) {
2576 MetaClassPtrAlias = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(
2577 IdTy->getElementType(), AS, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
2578 ".objc_metaclass_ref" + Class->getNameAsString(), &TheModule);
2579 }
2580 ReceiverClass = MetaClassPtrAlias;
2581 } else {
2582 if (!ClassPtrAlias) {
2583 ClassPtrAlias = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(
2584 IdTy->getElementType(), AS, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
2585 ".objc_class_ref" + Class->getNameAsString(), &TheModule);
2586 }
2587 ReceiverClass = ClassPtrAlias;
2588 }
2589 }
2590 // Cast the pointer to a simplified version of the class structure
2591 llvm::Type *CastTy = llvm::StructType::get(IdTy, IdTy);
2592 ReceiverClass = Builder.CreateBitCast(
2593 ReceiverClass, CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(CastTy));
2594 // Get the superclass pointer
2595 ReceiverClass = Builder.CreateStructGEP(CastTy, ReceiverClass, 1);
2596 // Load the superclass pointer
2597 ReceiverClass =
2598 Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ReceiverClass, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2599 }
2600 // Construct the structure used to look up the IMP
2601 llvm::StructType *ObjCSuperTy =
2602 llvm::StructType::get(Receiver->getType(), IdTy);
2603
2604 Address ObjCSuper = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(ObjCSuperTy,
2605 CGF.getPointerAlign());
2606
2607 Builder.CreateStore(Receiver, Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 0));
2608 Builder.CreateStore(ReceiverClass, Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 1));
2609
2610 ObjCSuper = EnforceType(Builder, ObjCSuper, PtrToObjCSuperTy);
2611
2612 // Get the IMP
2613 llvm::Value *imp = LookupIMPSuper(CGF, ObjCSuper, cmd, MSI);
2614 if (AS != 0)
2615 MSI.MessengerType =
2616 llvm::PointerType::get(MSI.MessengerType->getElementType(), AS);
2617 imp = EnforceType(Builder, imp, MSI.MessengerType);
2618
2619 llvm::Metadata *impMD[] = {
2620 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, Sel.getAsString()),
2621 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, Class->getSuperClass()->getNameAsString()),
2622 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
2623 llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), IsClassMessage))};
2624 llvm::MDNode *node = llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, impMD);
2625
2626 CGCallee callee(CGCalleeInfo(), imp);
2627
2628 llvm::CallBase *call;
2629 RValue msgRet = CGF.EmitCall(MSI.CallInfo, callee, Return, ActualArgs, &call);
2630 call->setMetadata(msgSendMDKind, node);
2631 return msgRet;
2632}
2633
2634/// Generate code for a message send expression.
2635RValue
2636CGObjCGNU::GenerateMessageSend(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2637 ReturnValueSlot Return,
2638 QualType ResultType,
2639 Selector Sel,
2640 llvm::Value *Receiver,
2641 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
2642 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
2643 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
2644 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2645
2646 // Strip out message sends to retain / release in GC mode
2647 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::GCOnly) {
2648 if (Sel == RetainSel || Sel == AutoreleaseSel) {
2649 return RValue::get(EnforceType(Builder, Receiver,
2650 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(ResultType)));
2651 }
2652 if (Sel == ReleaseSel) {
2653 return RValue::get(nullptr);
2654 }
2655 }
2656
2657 // If the return type is something that goes in an integer register, the
2658 // runtime will handle 0 returns. For other cases, we fill in the 0 value
2659 // ourselves.
2660 //
2661 // The language spec says the result of this kind of message send is
2662 // undefined, but lots of people seem to have forgotten to read that
2663 // paragraph and insist on sending messages to nil that have structure
2664 // returns. With GCC, this generates a random return value (whatever happens
2665 // to be on the stack / in those registers at the time) on most platforms,
2666 // and generates an illegal instruction trap on SPARC. With LLVM it corrupts
2667 // the stack.
2668 bool isPointerSizedReturn = (ResultType->isAnyPointerType() ||
2669 ResultType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() || ResultType->isVoidType());
2670
2671 llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = nullptr;
2672 llvm::BasicBlock *messageBB = nullptr;
2673 llvm::BasicBlock *continueBB = nullptr;
2674
2675 if (!isPointerSizedReturn) {
2676 startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2677 messageBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("msgSend");
2678 continueBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("continue");
2679
2680 llvm::Value *isNil = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Receiver,
2681 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Receiver->getType()));
2682 Builder.CreateCondBr(isNil, continueBB, messageBB);
2683 CGF.EmitBlock(messageBB);
2684 }
2685
2686 IdTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(ASTIdTy));
2687 llvm::Value *cmd;
2688 if (Method)
2689 cmd = GetSelector(CGF, Method);
2690 else
2691 cmd = GetSelector(CGF, Sel);
2692 cmd = EnforceType(Builder, cmd, SelectorTy);
2693 Receiver = EnforceType(Builder, Receiver, IdTy);
2694
2695 llvm::Metadata *impMD[] = {
2696 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, Sel.getAsString()),
2697 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, Class ? Class->getNameAsString() : ""),
2698 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
2699 llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), Class != nullptr))};
2700 llvm::MDNode *node = llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, impMD);
2701
2702 CallArgList ActualArgs;
2703 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(Receiver), ASTIdTy);
2704 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(cmd), CGF.getContext().getObjCSelType());
2705 ActualArgs.addFrom(CallArgs);
2706
2707 MessageSendInfo MSI = getMessageSendInfo(Method, ResultType, ActualArgs);
2708
2709 // Get the IMP to call
2710 llvm::Value *imp;
2711
2712 // If we have non-legacy dispatch specified, we try using the objc_msgSend()
2713 // functions. These are not supported on all platforms (or all runtimes on a
2714 // given platform), so we
2715 switch (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getObjCDispatchMethod()) {
2716 case CodeGenOptions::Legacy:
2717 imp = LookupIMP(CGF, Receiver, cmd, node, MSI);
2718 break;
2719 case CodeGenOptions::Mixed:
2720 case CodeGenOptions::NonLegacy:
2721 if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesFPRet(ResultType)) {
2722 imp =
2723 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(IdTy, IdTy, true),
2724 "objc_msgSend_fpret")
2725 .getCallee();
2726 } else if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesSRet(MSI.CallInfo)) {
2727 // The actual types here don't matter - we're going to bitcast the
2728 // function anyway
2729 imp =
2730 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(IdTy, IdTy, true),
2731 "objc_msgSend_stret")
2732 .getCallee();
2733 } else {
2734 imp = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
2735 llvm::FunctionType::get(IdTy, IdTy, true), "objc_msgSend")
2736 .getCallee();
2737 }
2738 // On CHERI, we must make sure that this call is not to an AS200 version
2739 // of the pointer, or we will end up deriving a DDC-relative capability,
2740 // which won't have the execute permission.
2741 MSI.MessengerType =
2742 llvm::PointerType::get(MSI.MessengerType->getElementType(), 0);
2743 }
2744
2745 // Reset the receiver in case the lookup modified it
2746 ActualArgs[0] = CallArg(RValue::get(Receiver), ASTIdTy);
2747
2748 imp = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(imp, MSI.MessengerType);
2749
2750 llvm::CallBase *call;
2751 CGCallee callee(CGCalleeInfo(), imp);
2752 RValue msgRet = CGF.EmitCall(MSI.CallInfo, callee, Return, ActualArgs, &call);
2753 call->setMetadata(msgSendMDKind, node);
2754
2755
2756 if (!isPointerSizedReturn) {
2757 messageBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2758 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(continueBB);
2759 CGF.EmitBlock(continueBB);
2760 if (msgRet.isScalar()) {
2761 llvm::Value *v = msgRet.getScalarVal();
2762 llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(v->getType(), 2);
2763 phi->addIncoming(v, messageBB);
2764 phi->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(v->getType()), startBB);
2765 msgRet = RValue::get(phi);
2766 } else if (msgRet.isAggregate()) {
2767 Address v = msgRet.getAggregateAddress();
2768 llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(v.getType(), 2);
2769 llvm::Type *RetTy = v.getElementType();
2770 Address NullVal = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(RetTy, v.getAlignment(), "null");
2771 CGF.InitTempAlloca(NullVal, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(RetTy));
2772 phi->addIncoming(v.getPointer(), messageBB);
2773 phi->addIncoming(NullVal.getPointer(), startBB);
2774 msgRet = RValue::getAggregate(Address(phi, v.getAlignment()));
2775 } else /* isComplex() */ {
2776 std::pair<llvm::Value*,llvm::Value*> v = msgRet.getComplexVal();
2777 llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(v.first->getType(), 2);
2778 phi->addIncoming(v.first, messageBB);
2779 phi->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(v.first->getType()),
2780 startBB);
2781 llvm::PHINode *phi2 = Builder.CreatePHI(v.second->getType(), 2);
2782 phi2->addIncoming(v.second, messageBB);
2783 phi2->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(v.second->getType()),
2784 startBB);
2785 msgRet = RValue::getComplex(phi, phi2);
2786 }
2787 }
2788 return msgRet;
2789}
2790
2791/// Generates a MethodList. Used in construction of a objc_class and
2792/// objc_category structures.
2793llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::
2794GenerateMethodList(StringRef ClassName,
2795 StringRef CategoryName,
2796 ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl*> Methods,
2797 bool isClassMethodList) {
2798 if (Methods.empty())
2799 return NULLPtr;
2800
2801 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
2802
2803 auto MethodList = Builder.beginStruct();
2804 MethodList.addNullPointer(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2805 MethodList.addInt(Int32Ty, Methods.size());
2806
2807 // Get the method structure type.
2808 llvm::StructType *ObjCMethodTy =
2809 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), {
2810 PtrToInt8Ty, // Really a selector, but the runtime creates it us.
2811 PtrToInt8Ty, // Method types
2812 IMPTy // Method pointer
2813 });
2814 bool isV2ABI = isRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GNUstep, 2);
2815 if (isV2ABI) {
2816 // size_t size;
2817 llvm::DataLayout td(&TheModule);
2818 MethodList.addInt(SizeTy, td.getTypeSizeInBits(ObjCMethodTy) /
2819 CGM.getContext().getCharWidth());
2820 ObjCMethodTy =
2821 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), {
2822 IMPTy, // Method pointer
2823 PtrToInt8Ty, // Selector
2824 PtrToInt8Ty // Extended type encoding
2825 });
2826 } else {
2827 ObjCMethodTy =
2828 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), {
2829 PtrToInt8Ty, // Really a selector, but the runtime creates it us.
2830 PtrToInt8Ty, // Method types
2831 IMPTy // Method pointer
2832 });
2833 }
2834 auto MethodArray = MethodList.beginArray();
2835 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
2836 for (const auto *OMD : Methods) {
2837 llvm::Constant *FnPtr =
2838 TheModule.getFunction(SymbolNameForMethod(ClassName, CategoryName,
2839 OMD->getSelector(),
2840 isClassMethodList));
2841 assert(FnPtr && "Can't generate metadata for method that doesn't exist");
2842 auto Method = MethodArray.beginStruct(ObjCMethodTy);
2843 if (isV2ABI) {
2844 Method.addBitCast(FnPtr, IMPTy);
2845 Method.add(GetConstantSelector(OMD->getSelector(),
2846 Context.getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(OMD)));
2847 Method.add(MakeConstantString(Context.getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(OMD, true)));
2848 } else {
2849 Method.add(MakeConstantString(OMD->getSelector().getAsString()));
2850 Method.add(MakeConstantString(Context.getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(OMD)));
2851 // LLVM requires functions to be in AS 0, but CHERI requires the IMP to be
2852 // in AS 200.
2853 Method.addPointerdBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(FnPtr, IMPTy);
2854 }
2855 Method.finishAndAddTo(MethodArray);
2856 }
2857 MethodArray.finishAndAddTo(MethodList);
2858
2859 // Create an instance of the structure
2860 return MethodList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_method_list",
2861 CGM.getPointerAlign());
2862}
2863
2864/// Generates an IvarList. Used in construction of a objc_class.
2865llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::
2866GenerateIvarList(ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> IvarNames,
2867 ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> IvarTypes,
2868 ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> IvarOffsets,
2869 ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> IvarAlign,
2870 ArrayRef<Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime> IvarOwnership) {
2871 if (IvarNames.empty())
2872 return NULLPtr;
2873
2874 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
2875
2876 // Structure containing array count followed by array.
2877 auto IvarList = Builder.beginStruct();
2878 IvarList.addInt(IntTy, (int)IvarNames.size());
2879
2880 // Get the ivar structure type.
2881 llvm::StructType *ObjCIvarTy =
2882 llvm::StructType::get(PtrToInt8Ty, PtrToInt8Ty, IntTy);
2883
2884 // Array of ivar structures.
2885 auto Ivars = IvarList.beginArray(ObjCIvarTy);
2886 for (unsigned int i = 0, e = IvarNames.size() ; i < e ; i++) {
2887 auto Ivar = Ivars.beginStruct(ObjCIvarTy);
2888 Ivar.add(IvarNames[i]);
2889 Ivar.add(IvarTypes[i]);
2890 Ivar.add(IvarOffsets[i]);
2891 Ivar.finishAndAddTo(Ivars);
2892 }
2893 Ivars.finishAndAddTo(IvarList);
2894
2895 // Create an instance of the structure
2896 return IvarList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_ivar_list",
2897 CGM.getPointerAlign());
2898}
2899
2900/// Generate a class structure
2901llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::GenerateClassStructure(
2902 llvm::Constant *MetaClass,
2903 llvm::Constant *SuperClass,
2904 unsigned info,
2905 const char *Name,
2906 llvm::Constant *Version,
2907 llvm::Constant *InstanceSize,
2908 llvm::Constant *IVars,
2909 llvm::Constant *Methods,
2910 llvm::Constant *Protocols,
2911 llvm::Constant *IvarOffsets,
2912 llvm::Constant *Properties,
2913 llvm::Constant *StrongIvarBitmap,
2914 llvm::Constant *WeakIvarBitmap,
2915 bool isMeta) {
2916 // Set up the class structure
2917 // Note: Several of these are char*s when they should be ids. This is
2918 // because the runtime performs this translation on load.
2919 //
2920 // Fields marked New ABI are part of the GNUstep runtime. We emit them
2921 // anyway; the classes will still work with the GNU runtime, they will just
2922 // be ignored.
2923 llvm::StructType *ClassTy = llvm::StructType::get(
2924 PtrToInt8Ty, // isa
2925 PtrToInt8Ty, // super_class
2926 PtrToInt8Ty, // name
2927 LongTy, // version
2928 LongTy, // info
2929 LongTy, // instance_size
2930 IVars->getType(), // ivars
2931 Methods->getType(), // methods
2932 // These are all filled in by the runtime, so we pretend
2933 PtrTy, // dtable
2934 PtrTy, // subclass_list
2935 PtrTy, // sibling_class
2936 PtrTy, // protocols
2937 PtrTy, // gc_object_type
2938 // New ABI:
2939 LongTy, // abi_version
2940 IvarOffsets->getType(), // ivar_offsets
2941 Properties->getType(), // properties
2942 PtrTy, // strong_pointers
2943 PtrTy // weak_pointers
2944 );
2945
2946 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
2947 auto Elements = Builder.beginStruct(ClassTy);
2948
2949 // Fill in the structure
2950
2951 // isa
2952 Elements.addBitCast(MetaClass, PtrToInt8Ty);
2953 // super_class
2954 Elements.add(SuperClass);
2955 // name
2956 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(Name, ".class_name"));
2957 // version
2958 Elements.addInt(LongTy, 0);
2959 // info
2960 Elements.addInt(LongTy, info);
2961 // instance_size
2962 if (isMeta) {
2963 llvm::DataLayout td(&TheModule);
2964 Elements.addInt(LongTy,
2965 td.getTypeSizeInBits(ClassTy) /
2966 CGM.getContext().getCharWidth());
2967 } else
2968 Elements.add(InstanceSize);
2969 // ivars
2970 Elements.add(IVars);
2971 // methods
2972 Elements.add(Methods);
2973 // These are all filled in by the runtime, so we pretend
2974 // dtable
2975 Elements.add(NULLPtr);
2976 // subclass_list
2977 Elements.add(NULLPtr);
2978 // sibling_class
2979 Elements.add(NULLPtr);
2980 // protocols
2981 Elements.addBitCast(Protocols, PtrTy);
2982 // gc_object_type
2983 Elements.add(NULLPtr);
2984 // abi_version
2985 Elements.addInt(LongTy, ClassABIVersion);
2986 // ivar_offsets
2987 Elements.add(IvarOffsets);
2988 // properties
2989 Elements.add(Properties);
2990 // strong_pointers
2991 Elements.add(StrongIvarBitmap);
2992 // weak_pointers
2993 Elements.add(WeakIvarBitmap);
2994 // Create an instance of the structure
2995 // This is now an externally visible symbol, so that we can speed up class
2996 // messages in the next ABI. We may already have some weak references to
2997 // this, so check and fix them properly.
2998 std::string ClassSym((isMeta ? "_OBJC_METACLASS_": "_OBJC_CLASS_") +
2999 std::string(Name));
3000 llvm::GlobalVariable *ClassRef = TheModule.getNamedGlobal(ClassSym);
3001 llvm::Constant *Class =
3002 Elements.finishAndCreateGlobal(ClassSym, CGM.getPointerAlign(), false,
3003 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
3004 if (ClassRef) {
3005 ClassRef->replaceAllUsesWith(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Class,
3006 ClassRef->getType()));
3007 ClassRef->removeFromParent();
3008 Class->setName(ClassSym);
3009 }
3010 return Class;
3011}
3012
3013llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::
3014GenerateProtocolMethodList(ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl*> Methods) {
3015 // Get the method structure type.
3016 llvm::StructType *ObjCMethodDescTy =
3017 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), { PtrToInt8Ty, PtrToInt8Ty });
3018 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3019 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3020 auto MethodList = Builder.beginStruct();
3021 MethodList.addInt(IntTy, Methods.size());
3022 auto MethodArray = MethodList.beginArray(ObjCMethodDescTy);
3023 for (auto *M : Methods) {
3024 auto Method = MethodArray.beginStruct(ObjCMethodDescTy);
3025 Method.add(MakeConstantString(M->getSelector().getAsString()));
3026 Method.add(MakeConstantString(Context.getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(M)));
3027 Method.finishAndAddTo(MethodArray);
3028 }
3029 MethodArray.finishAndAddTo(MethodList);
3030 return MethodList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_method_list",
3031 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3032}
3033
3034// Create the protocol list structure used in classes, categories and so on
3035llvm::Constant *
3036CGObjCGNU::GenerateProtocolList(ArrayRef<std::string> Protocols) {
3037
3038 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3039 auto ProtocolList = Builder.beginStruct();
3040 ProtocolList.add(NULLPtr);
3041 ProtocolList.addInt(LongTy, Protocols.size());
3042
3043 auto Elements = ProtocolList.beginArray(PtrToInt8Ty);
3044 for (const std::string *iter = Protocols.begin(), *endIter = Protocols.end();
3045 iter != endIter ; iter++) {
3046 llvm::Constant *protocol = nullptr;
3047 llvm::StringMap<llvm::Constant*>::iterator value =
3048 ExistingProtocols.find(*iter);
3049 if (value == ExistingProtocols.end()) {
3050 protocol = GenerateEmptyProtocol(*iter);
3051 } else {
3052 protocol = value->getValue();
3053 }
3054 Elements.addBitCast(protocol, PtrToInt8Ty);
3055 }
3056 Elements.finishAndAddTo(ProtocolList);
3057 return ProtocolList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_protocol_list",
3058 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3059}
3060
3061llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::GenerateProtocolRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3062 const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3063 llvm::Constant *&protocol = ExistingProtocols[PD->getNameAsString()];
3064 if (!protocol)
3065 GenerateProtocol(PD);
3066 llvm::Type *T =
3067 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().getObjCProtoType());
3068 unsigned AS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3069 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(protocol, llvm::PointerType::get(T, AS));
3070}
3071
3072llvm::Constant *
3073CGObjCGNU::GenerateEmptyProtocol(StringRef ProtocolName) {
3074 llvm::Constant *ProtocolList = GenerateProtocolList({});
3075 llvm::Constant *MethodList = GenerateProtocolMethodList({});
3076 MethodList = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(MethodList, PtrToInt8Ty);
3077 // Protocols are objects containing lists of the methods implemented and
3078 // protocols adopted.
3079 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3080 auto Elements = Builder.beginStruct();
3081
3082 // The isa pointer must be set to a magic number so the runtime knows it's
3083 // the correct layout.
3084 Elements.add(llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(
3085 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, ProtocolVersion), IdTy));
3086
3087 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(ProtocolName, ".objc_protocol_name"));
3088 Elements.add(ProtocolList); /* .protocol_list */
3089 Elements.add(MethodList); /* .instance_methods */
3090 Elements.add(MethodList); /* .class_methods */
3091 Elements.add(MethodList); /* .optional_instance_methods */
3092 Elements.add(MethodList); /* .optional_class_methods */
3093 Elements.add(NULLPtr); /* .properties */
3094 Elements.add(NULLPtr); /* .optional_properties */
3095 return Elements.finishAndCreateGlobal(SymbolForProtocol(ProtocolName),
3096 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3097}
3098
3099void CGObjCGNU::GenerateProtocol(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3100 std::string ProtocolName = PD->getNameAsString();
3101
3102 // Use the protocol definition, if there is one.
3103 if (const ObjCProtocolDecl *Def = PD->getDefinition())
3104 PD = Def;
3105
3106 SmallVector<std::string, 16> Protocols;
3107 for (const auto *PI : PD->protocols())
3108 Protocols.push_back(PI->getNameAsString());
3109 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> InstanceMethods;
3110 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> OptionalInstanceMethods;
3111 for (const auto *I : PD->instance_methods())
3112 if (I->isOptional())
3113 OptionalInstanceMethods.push_back(I);
3114 else
3115 InstanceMethods.push_back(I);
3116 // Collect information about class methods:
3117 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> ClassMethods;
3118 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> OptionalClassMethods;
3119 for (const auto *I : PD->class_methods())
3120 if (I->isOptional())
3121 OptionalClassMethods.push_back(I);
3122 else
3123 ClassMethods.push_back(I);
3124
3125 llvm::Constant *ProtocolList = GenerateProtocolList(Protocols);
3126 llvm::Constant *InstanceMethodList =
3127 GenerateProtocolMethodList(InstanceMethods);
3128 llvm::Constant *ClassMethodList =
3129 GenerateProtocolMethodList(ClassMethods);
3130 llvm::Constant *OptionalInstanceMethodList =
3131 GenerateProtocolMethodList(OptionalInstanceMethods);
3132 llvm::Constant *OptionalClassMethodList =
3133 GenerateProtocolMethodList(OptionalClassMethods);
3134
3135 // Property metadata: name, attributes, isSynthesized, setter name, setter
3136 // types, getter name, getter types.
3137 // The isSynthesized value is always set to 0 in a protocol. It exists to
3138 // simplify the runtime library by allowing it to use the same data
3139 // structures for protocol metadata everywhere.
3140
3141 llvm::Constant *PropertyList =
3142 GeneratePropertyList(nullptr, PD, false, false);
3143 llvm::Constant *OptionalPropertyList =
3144 GeneratePropertyList(nullptr, PD, false, true);
3145
3146 // Protocols are objects containing lists of the methods implemented and
3147 // protocols adopted.
3148 // The isa pointer must be set to a magic number so the runtime knows it's
3149 // the correct layout.
3150 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3151 auto Elements = Builder.beginStruct();
3152 Elements.add(
3153 llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(
3154 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, ProtocolVersion), IdTy));
3155 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(ProtocolName));
3156 Elements.add(ProtocolList);
3157 Elements.add(InstanceMethodList);
3158 Elements.add(ClassMethodList);
3159 Elements.add(OptionalInstanceMethodList);
3160 Elements.add(OptionalClassMethodList);
3161 Elements.add(PropertyList);
3162 Elements.add(OptionalPropertyList);
3163 ExistingProtocols[ProtocolName] =
3164 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
3165 Elements.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_protocol", CGM.getPointerAlign()),
3166 IdTy);
3167}
3168void CGObjCGNU::GenerateProtocolHolderCategory() {
3169 // Collect information about instance methods
3170
3171 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3172 auto Elements = Builder.beginStruct();
3173
3174 const std::string ClassName = "__ObjC_Protocol_Holder_Ugly_Hack";
3175 const std::string CategoryName = "AnotherHack";
3176 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(CategoryName));
3177 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(ClassName));
3178 // Instance method list
3179 Elements.addBitCast(GenerateMethodList(
3180 ClassName, CategoryName, {}, false), PtrTy);
3181 // Class method list
3182 Elements.addBitCast(GenerateMethodList(
3183 ClassName, CategoryName, {}, true), PtrTy);
3184
3185 // Protocol list
3186 ConstantInitBuilder ProtocolListBuilder(CGM);
3187 auto ProtocolList = ProtocolListBuilder.beginStruct();
3188 ProtocolList.add(NULLPtr);
3189 ProtocolList.addInt(LongTy, ExistingProtocols.size());
3190 auto ProtocolElements = ProtocolList.beginArray(PtrTy);
3191 for (auto iter = ExistingProtocols.begin(), endIter = ExistingProtocols.end();
3192 iter != endIter ; iter++) {
3193 ProtocolElements.addBitCast(iter->getValue(), PtrTy);
3194 }
3195 ProtocolElements.finishAndAddTo(ProtocolList);
3196 Elements.addBitCast(
3197 ProtocolList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_protocol_list",
3198 CGM.getPointerAlign()),
3199 PtrTy);
3200 Categories.push_back(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
3201 Elements.finishAndCreateGlobal("", CGM.getPointerAlign()),
3202 PtrTy));
3203}
3204
3205/// Libobjc2 uses a bitfield representation where small(ish) bitfields are
3206/// stored in a 64-bit value with the low bit set to 1 and the remaining 63
3207/// bits set to their values, LSB first, while larger ones are stored in a
3208/// structure of this / form:
3209///
3210/// struct { int32_t length; int32_t values[length]; };
3211///
3212/// The values in the array are stored in host-endian format, with the least
3213/// significant bit being assumed to come first in the bitfield. Therefore, a
3214/// bitfield with the 64th bit set will be (int64_t)&{ 2, [0, 1<<31] }, while a
3215/// bitfield / with the 63rd bit set will be 1<<64.
3216llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::MakeBitField(ArrayRef<bool> bits) {
3217 int bitCount = bits.size();
3218 int ptrBits = CGM.getTarget().getPointerRange(
3219 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
3220 if (bitCount < ptrBits) {
3221 uint64_t val = 1;
3222 for (int i=0 ; i<bitCount ; ++i) {
3223 if (bits[i]) val |= 1ULL<<(i+1);
3224 }
3225 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, val), PtrTy);
3226 }
3227 SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 8> values;
3228 int v=0;
3229 while (v < bitCount) {
3230 int32_t word = 0;
3231 for (int i=0 ; (i<32) && (v<bitCount) ; ++i) {
3232 if (bits[v]) word |= 1<<i;
3233 v++;
3234 }
3235 values.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, word));
3236 }
3237
3238 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3239 auto fields = builder.beginStruct();
3240 fields.addInt(Int32Ty, values.size());
3241 auto array = fields.beginArray();
3242 for (auto v : values) array.add(v);
3243 array.finishAndAddTo(fields);
3244
3245 llvm::Constant *GS =
3246 fields.finishAndCreateGlobal("", CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
3247 llvm::Constant *ptr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(GS, IntPtrTy);
3248 return ptr;
3249}

3254 for (const auto *PD : OCD->getReferencedProtocols())
3255 Protocols.push_back(PD->getNameAsString());

3259void CGObjCGNU::GenerateCategory(const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *OCD) {
3260 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = OCD->getClassInterface();
3261 std::string ClassName = Class->getNameAsString();
3262 std::string CategoryName = OCD->getNameAsString();
3263
3264 // Collect the names of referenced protocols
3265 const ObjCCategoryDecl *CatDecl = OCD->getCategoryDecl();
3266
3267 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3268 auto Elements = Builder.beginStruct();
3269 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(CategoryName));
3270 Elements.add(MakeConstantString(ClassName));
3271 // Instance method list
3272 SmallVector<ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> InstanceMethods;
3273 InstanceMethods.insert(InstanceMethods.begin(), OCD->instmeth_begin(),
3274 OCD->instmeth_end());
3275 Elements.addBitCast(
3276 GenerateMethodList(ClassName, CategoryName, InstanceMethods, false),
3277 PtrTy);
3278 // Class method list
3279
3280 SmallVector<ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> ClassMethods;
3281 ClassMethods.insert(ClassMethods.begin(), OCD->classmeth_begin(),
3282 OCD->classmeth_end());
3283 Elements.addBitCast(
3284 GenerateMethodList(ClassName, CategoryName, ClassMethods, true),
3285 PtrTy);
3286 // Protocol list
3287 Elements.addBitCast(GenerateCategoryProtocolList(CatDecl), PtrTy);
3288 if (isRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GNUstep, 2)) {
3289 const ObjCCategoryDecl *Category =
3290 Class->FindCategoryDeclaration(OCD->getIdentifier());
3291 if (Category) {
3292 // Instance properties
3293 Elements.addBitCast(GeneratePropertyList(OCD, Category, false), PtrTy);
3294 // Class properties
3295 Elements.addBitCast(GeneratePropertyList(OCD, Category, true), PtrTy);
3296 } else {
3297 Elements.addNullPointer(PtrTy);
3298 Elements.addNullPointer(PtrTy);
3299 }
3300 }
3301
3302 Categories.push_back(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
3303 Elements.finishAndCreateGlobal(
3304 std::string(".objc_category_")+ClassName+CategoryName,
3305 CGM.getPointerAlign()),
3306 PtrTy));
3307}
3308
3309llvm::Constant *CGObjCGNU::GeneratePropertyList(const Decl *Container,
3310 const ObjCContainerDecl *OCD,
3311 bool isClassProperty,
3312 bool protocolOptionalProperties) {
3313
3314 SmallVector<const ObjCPropertyDecl *, 16> Properties;
3315 llvm::SmallPtrSet<const IdentifierInfo*, 16> PropertySet;
3316 bool isProtocol = isa<ObjCProtocolDecl>(OCD);
3317 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3318
3319 std::function<void(const ObjCProtocolDecl *Proto)> collectProtocolProperties
3320 = [&](const ObjCProtocolDecl *Proto) {
3321 for (const auto *P : Proto->protocols())
3322 collectProtocolProperties(P);
3323 for (const auto *PD : Proto->properties()) {
3324 if (isClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3325 continue;
3326 // Skip any properties that are declared in protocols that this class
3327 // conforms to but are not actually implemented by this class.
3328 if (!isProtocol && !Context.getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(PD, Container))
3329 continue;
3330 if (!PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier()).second)
3331 continue;
3332 Properties.push_back(PD);
3333 }
3334 };
3335
3336 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(OCD))
3337 for (const ObjCCategoryDecl *ClassExt : OID->known_extensions())
3338 for (auto *PD : ClassExt->properties()) {
3339 if (isClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3340 continue;
3341 PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier());
3342 Properties.push_back(PD);
3343 }
3344
3345 for (const auto *PD : OCD->properties()) {
3346 if (isClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3347 continue;
3348 // If we're generating a list for a protocol, skip optional / required ones
3349 // when generating the other list.
3350 if (isProtocol && (protocolOptionalProperties != PD->isOptional()))
3351 continue;
3352 // Don't emit duplicate metadata for properties that were already in a
3353 // class extension.
3354 if (!PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier()).second)
3355 continue;
3356
3357 Properties.push_back(PD);
3358 }
3359
3360 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(OCD))
3361 for (const auto *P : OID->all_referenced_protocols())
3362 collectProtocolProperties(P);
3363 else if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *CD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(OCD))
3364 for (const auto *P : CD->protocols())
3365 collectProtocolProperties(P);
3366
3367 auto numProperties = Properties.size();
3368
3369 if (numProperties == 0)
3370 return NULLPtr;
3371
3372 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3373 auto propertyList = builder.beginStruct();
3374 auto properties = PushPropertyListHeader(propertyList, numProperties);
3375
3376 // Add all of the property methods need adding to the method list and to the
3377 // property metadata list.
3378 for (auto *property : Properties) {
3379 bool isSynthesized = false;
3380 bool isDynamic = false;
3381 if (!isProtocol) {
3382 auto *propertyImpl = Context.getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(property, Container);
3383 if (propertyImpl) {
3384 isSynthesized = (propertyImpl->getPropertyImplementation() ==
3385 ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize);
3386 isDynamic = (propertyImpl->getPropertyImplementation() ==
3387 ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Dynamic);
3388 }
3389 }
3390 PushProperty(properties, property, Container, isSynthesized, isDynamic);
3391 }
3392 properties.finishAndAddTo(propertyList);
3393
3394 return propertyList.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_property_list",
3395 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3396}

3398void CGObjCGNU::RegisterAlias(const ObjCCompatibleAliasDecl *OAD) {

3400 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassDecl =
3401 const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl *>(OAD->getClassInterface());
3402 ClassAliases.emplace_back(ClassDecl->getNameAsString(),
3403 OAD->getNameAsString());

3405
3406void CGObjCGNU::GenerateClass(const ObjCImplementationDecl *OID) {
3407 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3408
3409 // Get the superclass name.
3410 const ObjCInterfaceDecl * SuperClassDecl =
3411 OID->getClassInterface()->getSuperClass();
3412 std::string SuperClassName;
3413 if (SuperClassDecl) {
3414 SuperClassName = SuperClassDecl->getNameAsString();
3415 EmitClassRef(SuperClassName);
3416 }
3417 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3418
3419 // Get the class name
3420 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassDecl =
3421 const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl *>(OID->getClassInterface());
3422 std::string ClassName = ClassDecl->getNameAsString();
3423
3424 // Emit the symbol that is used to generate linker errors if this class is
3425 // referenced in other modules but not declared.
3426 std::string classSymbolName = "__objc_class_name_" + ClassName;
3427 if (auto *symbol = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(classSymbolName)) {
3428 symbol->setInitializer(llvm::ConstantInt::get(LongTy, 0));
3429 } else {
3430 new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, LongTy, false,
3431 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
3432 llvm::ConstantInt::get(LongTy, 0),
3433 classSymbolName, nullptr,
3434 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
3435 }
3436
3437 // Get the size of instances.
3438 int instanceSize =
3439 Context.getASTObjCImplementationLayout(OID).getSize().getQuantity();
3440
3441 // Collect information about instance variables.
3442 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> IvarNames;
3443 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> IvarTypes;
3444 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> IvarOffsets;
3445 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> IvarAligns;
3446 SmallVector<Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime, 16> IvarOwnership;
3447
3448 ConstantInitBuilder IvarOffsetBuilder(CGM);
3449 auto IvarOffsetValues = IvarOffsetBuilder.beginArray(PtrToIntTy);
3450 SmallVector<bool, 16> WeakIvars;
3451 SmallVector<bool, 16> StrongIvars;
3452
3453 int superInstanceSize = !SuperClassDecl ? 0 :
3454 Context.getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(SuperClassDecl).getSize().getQuantity();
3455 // For non-fragile ivars, set the instance size to 0 - {the size of just this
3456 // class}. The runtime will then set this to the correct value on load.
3457 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
3458 instanceSize = 0 - (instanceSize - superInstanceSize);
3459 }
3460
3461 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = ClassDecl->all_declared_ivar_begin(); IVD;
3462 IVD = IVD->getNextIvar()) {
3463 // Store the name
3464 IvarNames.push_back(MakeConstantString(IVD->getNameAsString()));
3465 // Get the type encoding for this ivar
3466 std::string TypeStr;
3467 Context.getObjCEncodingForType(IVD->getType(), TypeStr, IVD);
3468 IvarTypes.push_back(MakeConstantString(TypeStr));
3469 IvarAligns.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy,
3470 Context.getTypeSize(IVD->getType())));
3471 // Get the offset
3472 uint64_t BaseOffset = ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OID, IVD);
3473 uint64_t Offset = BaseOffset;
3474 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
3475 Offset = BaseOffset - superInstanceSize;
3476 }
3477 llvm::Constant *OffsetValue = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, Offset);
3478 // Create the direct offset value
3479 std::string OffsetName = "__objc_ivar_offset_value_" + ClassName +"." +
3480 IVD->getNameAsString();
3481
3482 llvm::GlobalVariable *OffsetVar = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(OffsetName);
3483 if (OffsetVar) {
3484 OffsetVar->setInitializer(OffsetValue);
3485 // If this is the real definition, change its linkage type so that
3486 // different modules will use this one, rather than their private
3487 // copy.
3488 OffsetVar->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
3489 } else
3490 OffsetVar = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, Int32Ty,
3491 false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
3492 OffsetValue, OffsetName, nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
3493 IvarOffsets.push_back(OffsetValue);
3494 IvarOffsetValues.add(OffsetVar);
3495 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lt = IVD->getType().getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime();
3496 IvarOwnership.push_back(lt);
3497 switch (lt) {
3498 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
3499 StrongIvars.push_back(true);
3500 WeakIvars.push_back(false);
3501 break;
3502 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
3503 StrongIvars.push_back(false);
3504 WeakIvars.push_back(true);
3505 break;
3506 default:
3507 StrongIvars.push_back(false);
3508 WeakIvars.push_back(false);
3509 }
3510 }
3511 llvm::Constant *StrongIvarBitmap = MakeBitField(StrongIvars);
3512 llvm::Constant *WeakIvarBitmap = MakeBitField(WeakIvars);
3513 llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetArray =
3514 IvarOffsetValues.finishAndCreateGlobal(".ivar.offsets",
3515 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3516
3517 // Collect information about instance methods
3518 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> InstanceMethods;
3519 InstanceMethods.insert(InstanceMethods.begin(), OID->instmeth_begin(),
3520 OID->instmeth_end());
3521
3522 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> ClassMethods;
3523 ClassMethods.insert(ClassMethods.begin(), OID->classmeth_begin(),
3524 OID->classmeth_end());
3525
3526 // Collect the same information about synthesized properties, which don't
3527 // show up in the instance method lists.
3528 for (auto *propertyImpl : OID->property_impls())
3529 if (propertyImpl->getPropertyImplementation() ==
3530 ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize) {
3531 ObjCPropertyDecl *property = propertyImpl->getPropertyDecl();
3532 auto addPropertyMethod = [&](const ObjCMethodDecl *accessor) {
3533 if (accessor)
3534 InstanceMethods.push_back(accessor);
3535 };
3536 addPropertyMethod(property->getGetterMethodDecl());
3537 addPropertyMethod(property->getSetterMethodDecl());
3538 }
3539
3540 llvm::Constant *Properties = GeneratePropertyList(OID, ClassDecl);
3541
3542 // Collect the names of referenced protocols
3543 SmallVector<std::string, 16> Protocols;
3544 for (const auto *I : ClassDecl->protocols())
3545 Protocols.push_back(I->getNameAsString());
3546
3547 // Get the superclass pointer.
3548 llvm::Constant *SuperClass;
3549 if (!SuperClassName.empty()) {
3550 SuperClass = MakeConstantString(SuperClassName, ".super_class_name");
3551 } else {
3552 SuperClass = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(PtrToInt8Ty);
3553 }
3554 // Empty vector used to construct empty method lists
3555 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 1> empty;
3556 // Generate the method and instance variable lists
3557 llvm::Constant *MethodList = GenerateMethodList(ClassName, "",
3558 InstanceMethods, false);
3559 llvm::Constant *ClassMethodList = GenerateMethodList(ClassName, "",
3560 ClassMethods, true);
3561 llvm::Constant *IvarList = GenerateIvarList(IvarNames, IvarTypes,
3562 IvarOffsets, IvarAligns, IvarOwnership);
3563 // Irrespective of whether we are compiling for a fragile or non-fragile ABI,
3564 // we emit a symbol containing the offset for each ivar in the class. This
3565 // allows code compiled for the non-Fragile ABI to inherit from code compiled
3566 // for the legacy ABI, without causing problems. The converse is also
3567 // possible, but causes all ivar accesses to be fragile.
3568
3569 // Offset pointer for getting at the correct field in the ivar list when
3570 // setting up the alias. These are: The base address for the global, the
3571 // ivar array (second field), the ivar in this list (set for each ivar), and
3572 // the offset (third field in ivar structure)
3573 llvm::Type *IndexTy = Int32Ty;
3574 llvm::Constant *offsetPointerIndexes[] = {Zeros[0],
3575 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, ClassABIVersion > 1 ? 2 : 1), nullptr,
3576 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, ClassABIVersion > 1 ? 3 : 2) };
3577
3578 unsigned ivarIndex = 0;
3579 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = ClassDecl->all_declared_ivar_begin(); IVD;
3580 IVD = IVD->getNextIvar()) {
3581 const std::string Name = GetIVarOffsetVariableName(ClassDecl, IVD);
3582 offsetPointerIndexes[2] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, ivarIndex);
3583 // Get the correct ivar field
3584 llvm::Constant *offsetValue = llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(
3585 cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(IvarList)->getValueType(), IvarList,
3586 offsetPointerIndexes);
3587 // Get the existing variable, if one exists.
3588 llvm::GlobalVariable *offset = TheModule.getNamedGlobal(Name);
3589 if (offset) {
3590 offset->setInitializer(offsetValue);
3591 // If this is the real definition, change its linkage type so that
3592 // different modules will use this one, rather than their private
3593 // copy.
3594 offset->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
3595 } else
3596 // Add a new alias if there isn't one already.
3597 new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, offsetValue->getType(),
3598 false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, offsetValue, Name,
3599 nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
3600 ++ivarIndex;
3601 }
3602 llvm::Constant *ZeroPtr = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(PtrTy);
3603
3604 //Generate metaclass for class methods
3605 llvm::Constant *MetaClassStruct = GenerateClassStructure(
3606 NULLPtr, NULLPtr, 0x12L, ClassName.c_str(), nullptr, Zeros[0],
3607 NULLPtr, ClassMethodList, NULLPtr, NULLPtr,
3608 GeneratePropertyList(OID, ClassDecl, true), ZeroPtr, ZeroPtr, true);
3609 CGM.setGVProperties(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(MetaClassStruct),
3610 OID->getClassInterface());
3611
3612 // Generate the class structure
3613 llvm::Constant *ClassStruct = GenerateClassStructure(
3614 MetaClassStruct, SuperClass, 0x11L, ClassName.c_str(), nullptr,
3615 llvm::ConstantInt::get(LongTy, instanceSize), IvarList, MethodList,
3616 GenerateProtocolList(Protocols), IvarOffsetArray, Properties,
3617 StrongIvarBitmap, WeakIvarBitmap);
3618 CGM.setGVProperties(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(ClassStruct),
3619 OID->getClassInterface());
3620
3621 // Resolve the class aliases, if they exist.
3622 if (ClassPtrAlias) {
3623 ClassPtrAlias->replaceAllUsesWith(
3624 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(ClassStruct, IdTy));
3625 ClassPtrAlias->eraseFromParent();
3626 ClassPtrAlias = nullptr;
3627 }
3628 if (MetaClassPtrAlias) {
3629 MetaClassPtrAlias->replaceAllUsesWith(
3630 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(MetaClassStruct, IdTy));
3631 MetaClassPtrAlias->eraseFromParent();
3632 MetaClassPtrAlias = nullptr;
3633 }
3634
3635 // Add class structure to list to be added to the symtab later
3636 ClassStruct = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(ClassStruct, PtrToInt8Ty);
3637 Classes.push_back(ClassStruct);
3638}
3639
3640llvm::Function *CGObjCGNU::ModuleInitFunction() {
3641 // Only emit an ObjC load function if no Objective-C stuff has been called
3642 if (Classes.empty() && Categories.empty() && ConstantStrings.empty() &&
3643 ExistingProtocols.empty() && SelectorTable.empty())
3644 return nullptr;
3645
3646 // Add all referenced protocols to a category.
3647 GenerateProtocolHolderCategory();
3648 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3649
3650 llvm::StructType *selStructTy =
3651 dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(SelectorTy->getElementType());
3652 llvm::Type *selStructPtrTy = SelectorTy;
3653 if (!selStructTy) {
3654 selStructTy = llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3655 { PtrToInt8Ty, PtrToInt8Ty });
3656 selStructPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(selStructTy, AS);
3657 }
3658
3659 // Generate statics list:
3660 llvm::Constant *statics = NULLPtr;
3661 if (!ConstantStrings.empty()) {
3662 llvm::GlobalVariable *fileStatics = [&] {
3663 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3664 auto staticsStruct = builder.beginStruct();
3665
3666 StringRef stringClass = CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCConstantStringClass;
3667 if (stringClass.empty()) stringClass = "NXConstantString";
3668 staticsStruct.add(MakeConstantString(stringClass,
3669 ".objc_static_class_name"));
3670
3671 auto array = staticsStruct.beginArray();
3672 array.addAll(ConstantStrings);
3673 array.add(NULLPtr);
3674 array.finishAndAddTo(staticsStruct);
3675
3676 return staticsStruct.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_statics",
3677 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3678 }();
3679
3680 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3681 auto allStaticsArray = builder.beginArray(fileStatics->getType());
3682 allStaticsArray.add(fileStatics);
3683 allStaticsArray.addNullPointer(fileStatics->getType());
3684
3685 statics = allStaticsArray.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_statics_ptr",
3686 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3687 statics = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(statics, PtrTy);
3688 }
3689
3690 // Array of classes, categories, and constant objects.
3691
3692 SmallVector<llvm::GlobalAlias*, 16> selectorAliases;
3693 unsigned selectorCount;
3694
3695 // Pointer to an array of selectors used in this module.
3696 llvm::GlobalVariable *selectorList = [&] {
3697 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3698 auto selectors = builder.beginArray(selStructTy);
3699 auto &table = SelectorTable; // MSVC workaround
3700 std::vector<Selector> allSelectors;
3701 for (auto &entry : table)
3702 allSelectors.push_back(entry.first);
3703 llvm::sort(allSelectors);
3704
3705 for (auto &untypedSel : allSelectors) {
3706 std::string selNameStr = untypedSel.getAsString();
3707 llvm::Constant *selName = ExportUniqueString(selNameStr, ".objc_sel_name");
3708
3709 for (TypedSelector &sel : table[untypedSel]) {
3710 llvm::Constant *selectorTypeEncoding = NULLPtr;
3711 if (!sel.first.empty())
3712 selectorTypeEncoding =
3713 MakeConstantString(sel.first, ".objc_sel_types");
3714
3715 auto selStruct = selectors.beginStruct(selStructTy);
3716 selStruct.add(selName);
3717 selStruct.add(selectorTypeEncoding);
3718 selStruct.finishAndAddTo(selectors);
3719
3720 // Store the selector alias for later replacement
3721 selectorAliases.push_back(sel.second);
3722 }
3723 }
3724
3725 // Remember the number of entries in the selector table.
3726 selectorCount = selectors.size();
3727
3728 // NULL-terminate the selector list. This should not actually be required,
3729 // because the selector list has a length field. Unfortunately, the GCC
3730 // runtime decides to ignore the length field and expects a NULL terminator,
3731 // and GCC cooperates with this by always setting the length to 0.
3732 auto selStruct = selectors.beginStruct(selStructTy);
3733 selStruct.add(NULLPtr);
3734 selStruct.add(NULLPtr);
3735 selStruct.finishAndAddTo(selectors);
3736
3737 return selectors.finishAndCreateGlobal(".objc_selector_list",
3738 CGM.getPointerAlign());
3739 }();
3740
3741 // Now that all of the static selectors exist, create pointers to them.
3742 for (unsigned i = 0; i < selectorCount; ++i) {
3743 llvm::Constant *idxs[] = {
3744 Zeros[0],
3745 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, i)
3746 };
3747 // FIXME: We're generating redundant loads and stores here!
3748 llvm::Constant *selPtr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(
3749 selectorList->getValueType(), selectorList, idxs);
3750 // If selectors are defined as an opaque type, cast the pointer to this
3751 // type.
3752 selPtr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(selPtr, SelectorTy);
3753 selectorAliases[i]->replaceAllUsesWith(selPtr);
3754 selectorAliases[i]->eraseFromParent();
3755 }
3756
3757 llvm::GlobalVariable *symtab = [&] {
3758 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3759 auto symtab = builder.beginStruct();
3760
3761 // Number of static selectors
3762 symtab.addInt(LongTy, selectorCount);
3763
3764 symtab.addBitCast(selectorList, selStructPtrTy);
3765
3766 // Number of classes defined.
3767 symtab.addInt(CGM.Int16Ty, Classes.size());
3768 // Number of categories defined
3769 symtab.addInt(CGM.Int16Ty, Categories.size());
3770
3771 // Create an array of classes, then categories, then static object instances
3772 auto classList = symtab.beginArray(PtrToInt8Ty);
3773 classList.addAll(Classes);
3774 classList.addAll(Categories);
3775 // NULL-terminated list of static object instances (mainly constant strings)
3776 classList.add(statics);
3777 classList.add(NULLPtr);
3778 classList.finishAndAddTo(symtab);
3779
3780 // Construct the symbol table.
3781 return symtab.finishAndCreateGlobal("", CGM.getPointerAlign());
3782 }();
3783
3784 // The symbol table is contained in a module which has some version-checking
3785 // constants
3786 llvm::PointerType *symtabTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(symtab->getType());
3787 llvm::Constant *module = [&] {
3788 llvm::Type *moduleEltTys[] = {
3789 LongTy, LongTy, PtrToInt8Ty, llvm::PointerType::get(symtabTy->getElementType(), AS), IntTy
3790 };
3791 llvm::StructType *moduleTy =
3792 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3793 makeArrayRef(moduleEltTys).drop_back(unsigned(RuntimeVersion < 10)));
3794
3795 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3796 auto module = builder.beginStruct(moduleTy);
3797 // Runtime version, used for ABI compatibility checking.
3798 module.addInt(LongTy, RuntimeVersion);
3799 // sizeof(ModuleTy)
3800 module.addInt(LongTy, CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(moduleTy));
3801
3802 // The path to the source file where this module was declared
3803 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
3804 const FileEntry *mainFile = SM.getFileEntryForID(SM.getMainFileID());
3805 std::string path =
3806 (Twine(mainFile->getDir()->getName()) + "/" + mainFile->getName()).str();
3807 module.add(MakeConstantString(path, ".objc_source_file_name"));
3808 module.add(symtab);
3809
3810 if (RuntimeVersion >= 10) {
3811 switch (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC()) {
3812 case LangOptions::GCOnly:
3813 module.addInt(IntTy, 2);
3814 break;
3815 case LangOptions::NonGC:
3816 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
3817 module.addInt(IntTy, 1);
3818 else
3819 module.addInt(IntTy, 0);
3820 break;
3821 case LangOptions::HybridGC:
3822 module.addInt(IntTy, 1);
3823 break;
3824 }
3825 }
3826
3827 return module.finishAndCreateGlobal("", CGM.getPointerAlign());
3828 }();
3829
3830 // Create the load function calling the runtime entry point with the module
3831 // structure
3832 llvm::Function * LoadFunction = llvm::Function::Create(
3833 llvm::FunctionType::get(llvm::Type::getVoidTy(VMContext), false),
3834 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, ".objc_load_function",
3835 &TheModule);
3836 llvm::BasicBlock *EntryBB =
3837 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(VMContext, "entry", LoadFunction);
3838 CGBuilderTy Builder(CGM, VMContext);
3839 Builder.SetInsertPoint(EntryBB);
3840
3841 llvm::PointerType *moduleTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(module->getType());
3842 llvm::FunctionType *FT =
3843 llvm::FunctionType::get(Builder.getVoidTy(), llvm::PointerType::get(moduleTy->getElementType(), AS), true);
3844 llvm::FunctionCallee Register =
3845 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FT, "__objc_exec_class");
3846 Builder.CreateCall(Register, module);
3847
3848 if (!ClassAliases.empty()) {
3849 llvm::Type *ArgTypes[2] = {PtrTy, PtrToInt8Ty};
3850 llvm::FunctionType *RegisterAliasTy =
3851 llvm::FunctionType::get(Builder.getVoidTy(),
3852 ArgTypes, false);
3853 llvm::Function *RegisterAlias = llvm::Function::Create(
3854 RegisterAliasTy,
3855 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage, "class_registerAlias_np",
3856 &TheModule);
3857 llvm::BasicBlock *AliasBB =
3858 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(VMContext, "alias", LoadFunction);
3859 llvm::BasicBlock *NoAliasBB =
3860 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(VMContext, "no_alias", LoadFunction);
3861
3862 // Branch based on whether the runtime provided class_registerAlias_np()
3863 llvm::Value *HasRegisterAlias = Builder.CreateICmpNE(RegisterAlias,
3864 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(RegisterAlias->getType()));
3865 Builder.CreateCondBr(HasRegisterAlias, AliasBB, NoAliasBB);
3866
3867 // The true branch (has alias registration function):
3868 Builder.SetInsertPoint(AliasBB);
3869 // Emit alias registration calls:
3870 for (std::vector<ClassAliasPair>::iterator iter = ClassAliases.begin();
3871 iter != ClassAliases.end(); ++iter) {
3872 llvm::Constant *TheClass =
3873 TheModule.getGlobalVariable("_OBJC_CLASS_" + iter->first, true);
3874 if (TheClass) {
3875 TheClass = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(TheClass, PtrTy);
3876 Builder.CreateCall(RegisterAlias,
3877 {TheClass, MakeConstantString(iter->second)});
3878 }
3879 }
3880 // Jump to end:
3881 Builder.CreateBr(NoAliasBB);
3882
3883 // Missing alias registration function, just return from the function:
3884 Builder.SetInsertPoint(NoAliasBB);
3885 }
3886 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3887
3888 return LoadFunction;
3889}

3891llvm::Function *CGObjCGNU::GenerateMethod(const ObjCMethodDecl *OMD,
3892 const ObjCContainerDecl *CD) {
3893 const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *OCD =
3894 dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(OMD->getDeclContext());
3895 StringRef CategoryName = OCD ? OCD->getName() : "";
3896 StringRef ClassName = CD->getName();
3897 Selector MethodName = OMD->getSelector();
3898 bool isClassMethod = !OMD->isInstanceMethod();
3899
3900 CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
3901 llvm::FunctionType *MethodTy =
3902 Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeObjCMethodDeclaration(OMD));
3903 std::string FunctionName = SymbolNameForMethod(ClassName, CategoryName,
3904 MethodName, isClassMethod);
3905
3906 llvm::Function *Method
3907 = llvm::Function::Create(MethodTy,
3908 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3909 FunctionName,
3910 &TheModule);
3911 return Method;
3912}

3952
3953void CGObjCGNU::EmitTryStmt(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3954 const ObjCAtTryStmt &S) {
3955 // Unlike the Apple non-fragile runtimes, which also uses
3956 // unwind-based zero cost exceptions, the GNU Objective C runtime's
3957 // EH support isn't a veneer over C++ EH. Instead, exception
3958 // objects are created by objc_exception_throw and destroyed by
3959 // the personality function; this avoids the need for bracketing
3960 // catch handlers with calls to __blah_begin_catch/__blah_end_catch
3961 // (or even _Unwind_DeleteException), but probably doesn't
3962 // interoperate very well with foreign exceptions.
3963 //
3964 // In Objective-C++ mode, we actually emit something equivalent to the C++
3965 // exception handler.
3966 EmitTryCatchStmt(CGF, S, EnterCatchFn, ExitCatchFn, ExceptionReThrowFn);
3967}
3968
3969void CGObjCGNU::EmitThrowStmt(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3970 const ObjCAtThrowStmt &S,
3971 bool ClearInsertionPoint) {
3972 llvm::Value *ExceptionAsObject;
3973 bool isRethrow = false;
3974
3975 if (const Expr *ThrowExpr = S.getThrowExpr()) {
3976 llvm::Value *Exception = CGF.EmitObjCThrowOperand(ThrowExpr);
3977 ExceptionAsObject = Exception;
3978 } else {
3979 assert((!CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.empty() && CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.back()) &&
3980 "Unexpected rethrow outside @catch block.");
3981 ExceptionAsObject = CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.back();
3982 isRethrow = true;
3983 }
3984 if (isRethrow && usesSEHExceptions) {
3985 // For SEH, ExceptionAsObject may be undef, because the catch handler is
3986 // not passed it for catchalls and so it is not visible to the catch
3987 // funclet. The real thrown object will still be live on the stack at this
3988 // point and will be rethrown. If we are explicitly rethrowing the object
3989 // that was passed into the `@catch` block, then this code path is not
3990 // reached and we will instead call `objc_exception_throw` with an explicit
3991 // argument.
3992 llvm::CallBase *Throw = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ExceptionReThrowFn);
3993 Throw->setDoesNotReturn();
3994 }
3995 else {
3996 ExceptionAsObject = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ExceptionAsObject, IdTy);
3997 llvm::CallBase *Throw =
3998 CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ExceptionThrowFn, ExceptionAsObject);
3999 Throw->setDoesNotReturn();
4000 }
4001 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4002 if (ClearInsertionPoint)
4003 CGF.Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
4004}

4006llvm::Value * CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCWeakRead(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4007 Address AddrWeakObj) {
4008 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;
4009 AddrWeakObj = EnforceType(B, AddrWeakObj, PtrToIdTy);
4010 return B.CreateCall(WeakReadFn, AddrWeakObj.getPointer());
4011}

4013void CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCWeakAssign(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4014 llvm::Value *src, Address dst) {
4015 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;
4016 src = EnforceType(B, src, IdTy);
4017 dst = EnforceType(B, dst, PtrToIdTy);
4018 B.CreateCall(WeakAssignFn, {src, dst.getPointer()});
4019}

4021void CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCGlobalAssign(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4022 llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
4023 bool threadlocal) {
4024 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;

4031
4032void CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCIvarAssign(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4033 llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
4034 llvm::Value *ivarOffset) {
4035 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;
4036 src = EnforceType(B, src, IdTy);
4037 dst = EnforceType(B, dst, IdTy);
4038 B.CreateCall(IvarAssignFn, {src, dst.getPointer(), ivarOffset});
4039}
4040
4041void CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCStrongCastAssign(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4042 llvm::Value *src, Address dst) {
4043 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;
4044 src = EnforceType(B, src, IdTy);
4045 dst = EnforceType(B, dst, PtrToIdTy);
4046 B.CreateCall(StrongCastAssignFn, {src, dst.getPointer()});
4047}
4048
4049void CGObjCGNU::EmitGCMemmoveCollectable(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4050 Address DestPtr,
4051 Address SrcPtr,
4052 llvm::Value *Size) {
4053 CGBuilderTy &B = CGF.Builder;
4054 DestPtr = EnforceType(B, DestPtr, PtrTy);
4055 SrcPtr = EnforceType(B, SrcPtr, PtrTy);
4056
4057 B.CreateCall(MemMoveFn, {DestPtr.getPointer(), SrcPtr.getPointer(), Size});
4058}
4059
4060llvm::GlobalVariable *CGObjCGNU::ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(
4061 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
4062 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
4063 const std::string Name = GetIVarOffsetVariableName(ID, Ivar);
4064 // Emit the variable and initialize it with what we think the correct value
4065 // is. This allows code compiled with non-fragile ivars to work correctly
4066 // when linked against code which isn't (most of the time).
4067 llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetPointer = TheModule.getNamedGlobal(Name);
4068 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
4069 if (!IvarOffsetPointer)
4070 IvarOffsetPointer = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule,
4071 llvm::Type::getInt32PtrTy(VMContext, AS), false,
4072 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr, Name);
4073 return IvarOffsetPointer;
4074}
4075
4076LValue CGObjCGNU::EmitObjCValueForIvar(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4077 QualType ObjectTy,
4078 llvm::Value *BaseValue,
4079 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar,
4080 unsigned CVRQualifiers) {
4081 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID =
4082 ObjectTy->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()->getInterface();
4083 return EmitValueForIvarAtOffset(CGF, ID, BaseValue, Ivar, CVRQualifiers,
4084 EmitIvarOffset(CGF, ID, Ivar));
4085}
4086
4087static const ObjCInterfaceDecl *FindIvarInterface(ASTContext &Context,
4088 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID,
4089 const ObjCIvarDecl *OIVD) {
4090 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *next = OID->all_declared_ivar_begin(); next;
4091 next = next->getNextIvar()) {
4092 if (OIVD == next)
4093 return OID;
4094 }
4095
4096 // Otherwise check in the super class.
4097 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = OID->getSuperClass())
4098 return FindIvarInterface(Context, Super, OIVD);
4099
4100 return nullptr;
4101}
4102
4103llvm::Value *CGObjCGNU::EmitIvarOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4104 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface,
4105 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
4106 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
4107 Interface = FindIvarInterface(CGM.getContext(), Interface, Ivar);
4108
4109 // The MSVC linker cannot have a single global defined as LinkOnceAnyLinkage
4110 // and ExternalLinkage, so create a reference to the ivar global and rely on
4111 // the definition being created as part of GenerateClass.
4112 if (RuntimeVersion < 10 ||
4113 CGF.CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isKnownWindowsMSVCEnvironment())
4114 return CGF.Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(
4115 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
4116 Int32Ty, CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
4117 ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(Interface, Ivar),
4118 CGF.getPointerAlign(), "ivar"),
4119 CharUnits::fromQuantity(4)),
4120 PtrDiffTy);
4121 std::string name = "__objc_ivar_offset_value_" +
4122 Interface->getNameAsString() +"." + Ivar->getNameAsString();
4123 CharUnits Align = CGM.getIntAlign();
4124 llvm::Value *Offset = TheModule.getGlobalVariable(name);
4125 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
4126 if (!Offset) {
4127 auto GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(TheModule, IntTy,
4128 false, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage,
4129 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(IntTy), name, nullptr,
4130 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AS);
4131 GV->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
4132 Offset = GV;
4133 }
4134 Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Offset, Align);
4135 if (Offset->getType() != PtrDiffTy)
4136 Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(Offset, PtrDiffTy);
4137 return Offset;
4138 }
4139 uint64_t Offset = ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGF.CGM, Interface, Ivar);
4140 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(PtrDiffTy, Offset, /*isSigned*/true);
4141}
4142
4143CGObjCRuntime *
4144clang::CodeGen::CreateGNUObjCRuntime(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4145 auto Runtime = CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime;
4146 switch (Runtime.getKind()) {
4147 case ObjCRuntime::GNUstep:
4148 if (Runtime.getVersion() >= VersionTuple(2, 0))
4149 return new CGObjCGNUstep2(CGM);
4150 return new CGObjCGNUstep(CGM);
4151
4152 case ObjCRuntime::GCC:
4153 return new CGObjCGCC(CGM);
4154
4155 case ObjCRuntime::ObjFW:
4156 return new CGObjCObjFW(CGM);
4157
4158 case ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX:
4159 case ObjCRuntime::MacOSX:
4160 case ObjCRuntime::iOS:
4161 case ObjCRuntime::WatchOS:
4162 llvm_unreachable("these runtimes are not GNU runtimes");
4163 }
4164 llvm_unreachable("bad runtime");
4165}
